<center>


== History ==
<center>
The XONE is an organization that dates back to World War II in the Frontrooms. The XONE was formed by a group of Nazi soldiers and officials who no-clipped into the Backrooms. The XONE was a classified group; high-ranking officials and Hitler himself were oblivious to its formation.<br><br>After seeing the devastating effects of multiple battles during World War II, a few Nazis from the Nazi regime defected and formed what they called the XONE, aiming to stop the bloodshed that World War II had caused. They later expanded their group by taking in refugees from war or persuading other members of the Nazi Party to join their cause.  

After World War II, the XONE hid in their underground facility at the Auschwitz-Birkenau testing facilities, as many of them had previous affiliations to the Nazi Party and would be executed for committing war crimes under Hitler with no evidence supporting their innocence. Their goal was to eliminate what remained of the Nazi Party after seeing their downfall. Their true goal was later realized when a large rift opened in the testing facilities, bringing a large portion of the XONE into a [[Backrooms Wiki|labyrinth of mono-yellow halls]]. Many of the XONE's members have rejected Hitler's ideology, as they believe that the cruelty to the Jewish population was unjust. Due to this fact, XONE has rejected many claims that relate them to Nazism. 

Since then, many members of the XONE hold very different beliefs, which have been outlined below. 


== Their Mission ==
<center>
The XONE holds the belief that humans are a supreme world power and should eradicate those that stand in their way. They believe that all humans are valuable and useful, regardless of their racial group. Thus, the XONE has embarked on a mission to document everything anomalous in the Backrooms so as to purge the Backrooms of all harmful entities and, in turn, destroy the Backrooms itself. However, many missions of the XONE have resulted in failure due to the anomalous nature of the Backrooms.

Examples of such outstanding missions have been pinned down below.


== XONE personnel ==

<span style="font-family: 'Cinzel Decorative' ; font-size:20px; ">=== Scouts ===</span>
<center>The scouts are of the lowest rank in the XONE. The only job they have is to explore the Backrooms and discover and document new entities. In any major conflict or battle, the Scouts have the goal of sneaking past enemy lines to assess any threats and report back to the XONE.  Unfortunately, normal firepower is not enough to counter and capture most entities in the Backrooms. As such, the XONE use more advanced weaponry and send in more skilled troops. 




The Scouts are usually equipped with steel-reinforced nets, a downsized version of the Erma EMP, and the Beretta M1934. They carry weapons that weigh less and minimize the load that they carry to ensure maximum mobility. The scouts wear standard-issue XONE uniforms and don MCU-2/P gas masks. During special missions, the Scouts may wear civilian clothing to disguise themselves as normal wanderers. 

Scouts have basic martial arts training and are selected through a test, identifying only the quickest and most agile soldiers.
----


<span style="font-family: 'Cinzel Decorative' ; font-size:20px; ">=== Heavy Scouts ===</span>
<center>
Heavy Scouts are well-armed soldiers that wield more advanced weapons and undergo stricter training than regular Scouts. They bear lightweight weapons with high explosive power, such as grenades and trip mines. They have fighting strategies similar to that of [[Party Crashers]], such as using solidified [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] or oscillating a bottle of Greek Fire to spray it on entities. They are given harder and riskier missions, such as capturing deadly entities or exploring Class 3 to Class 4 levels. 

They are recognized by their gas masks and standard-issue uniforms. However, they are mostly seen wearing bulletproof vests and heavy mud boots. They usually face the most casualties, as their missions are incredibly hard and dangerous.
----


<span style="font-family: 'Cinzel Decorative' ; font-size:20px; ">=== Bodyguards ===</span>

Bodyguards are personal guards of the scientists, researchers, and the Chairman of XONE. The bodyguards originate from the ''Schutzstaffel,'' Hitler's personal bodyguards. They are elite soldiers of the XONE; unlike scouts, they do not hold sophisticated weapons; instead, they hold only a Glock-19 and an assortment of knives and grenades. They have been taught judo, taekwondo, American wrestling, and boxing. 

They wear heavy-duty armor and are usually tasked to protect their assigned person with their life. They also accompany supply shipments to other outposts to ensure the safe delivery of valuable resources. 
----


<span style="font-family: 'Cinzel Decorative' ; font-size:20px; ">=== Researchers ===</span>

The researchers/scientists are one of the highest ranks of the XONE. They usually work with volatile objects and dangerous entities, documenting various phenomena across the Backrooms. They have taken an interest in the [[Entity 9|Facelings']] intelligence and ability to feel emotion. They are currently debating among themselves whether they should be given human rights and thus permanent exclusion from the XONE's harsh experiments.

They are accompanied by two bodyguards and two heavy scouts. Most of the spending of the XONE's budget is allocated to the area of research due to their belief that the use of science is the only way to defend themselves from the anomalous evils in the Backrooms.
----


<span style="font-family: 'Cinzel Decorative' ; font-size:20px; ">==== -The Chairman (Tillmann Rickenbacker) ====</span>

The chairman is the leader of the entire XONE. He has the belief that any other beings than humans are below him, not even seeing the friendly entities of the Backrooms as equals. Upon the discovery of the Backrooms, he ordered the immediate study of the unknown life forms here. After learning that one of his soldiers had died to an unknown entity, he doubled down on his decision to eliminate all hostiles in the Backrooms. Despite his prejudice toward living creatures that were not considered human, he is sympathetic and cares deeply for others.

Despite his flawed morals, Tillman Rickenbacker is an extremely intelligent person, having orchestrated several successful attacks on the Partygoers and other entity groups in the Backrooms, even rivaling that of [[Caius Taggert|Caius Taggert's]] ability.  He is a professional in biology and a master at chemical warfare with a high level of strategy.

However, he is not strong or agile, never fighting on the frontlines himself or putting himself into any immediate risk or danger. 

Additionally, he has a hatred toward the Cultis Sancti. A cult in [[level 1]], they have once killed a core member of the XONE, and is one of the groups Tillman seeks to d<span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS' ; font-size:10; "></span>estroy.{{Blurquote|image=greyey.png|quote-text=-  Science is the only thing left in this dimension to turn the tables on Evil.|person=Tillman Rickenbacker|font-size=10}}



